{
  "message": "fuzz(openfs-mvcc-wal-recovery): 19 structured seeds across SeedCase \u00d7\nfail_fast \u00d7 payload extremes\n\nfuzz_openfs_mvcc_wal_recovery drives mount-time WAL recovery against\nsix fabricated WAL shapes (Clean / TruncatedTail / CorruptHeader /\nMonotonicityViolation / EmptyFile / NoWalPath) with a fail_fast bool\nthat flips between best-effort recovery and the strict \"FailFast must\nnot leave visible MVCC versions or block contents\" contract. The\nexisting 3 ad-hoc seeds (clean, monotonic, truncated) covered only\nthree of those six SeedCase variants and never exercised the fail_fast\nbool or the post-base mutate_bytes pass.\n\nAdds 19 seeds covering:\n\n  Each SeedCase \u00d7 fail_fast combination:\n  * Clean: best_effort + fail_fast\n  * TruncatedTail: small chop / max chop (chop=7) / fail_fast\n  * CorruptHeader: 1-byte truncation / 11-byte (just below\n    WAL_HEADER_SIZE) / fail_fast\n  * MonotonicityViolation: best_effort + fail_fast\n  * EmptyFile: best_effort + fail_fast\n  * NoWalPath: best_effort + fail_fast\n\n  Payload extremes for the Clean shape:\n  * max_payload (len_a=24, len_b=24, extra_len=7) \u2014 drives the\n    largest commits the harness can emit\n  * min_payload (every length byte at 1) \u2014 minimum legal commit\n\n  Mutate_bytes pass coverage:\n  * Clean + 3 byte flips at the interesting-offset table (offsets\n    0, WAL_HEADER_SIZE-1, bytes.len()-1)\n  * Clean + 6-byte append (replay must treat the trailing bytes as\n    truncated-tail)\n  * TruncatedTail + 1 flip at WAL_HEADER_SIZE (combined chop+flip\n    surface)\n\nValidated with `-runs=0` over the 22 corpus inputs: all load cleanly,\ncoverage rises to 1 046 PCs / 1 342 features.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>",
